{"id":859591720,"question_id":13,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1 year, 6 months","timestamp":1671007218,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"10 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/859591720/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"43 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public int romanToInt(String s) {\n        HashMap<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();\n        map.put(\"IX\", 9);\n        map.put(\"IV\", 4);\n        map.put(\"XL\", 40);\n        map.put(\"XC\", 90);\n        map.put(\"CD\", 400);\n        map.put(\"CM\", 900);\n        \n        \n        \n        \n        \n        int res =0;\n        \n        for(Map.Entry<String, Integer> en : map.entrySet()){\n            \n            while(s.contains(en.getKey())){\n                s = s.replace(en.getKey(), \"\");\n                res+=en.getValue();\n            }\n        }\n        \n        map.put(\"I\", 1);\n        map.put(\"V\", 5);\n        map.put(\"X\", 10);\n        map.put(\"L\", 50);\n        map.put(\"C\", 100);\n        map.put(\"D\", 500);\n        map.put(\"M\", 1000);\n        \n        \n        for(char c : s.toCharArray()){\n            res+=map.get(String.valueOf(c));\n        }\n        \n        \n        return res;   \n        \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
